<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/62a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2865. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName>
                            from <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>:</p>
                        <p>Our wheat situation is such that we simply cannot supply Switzerland. We
                            can send some barley and rye for present and after January 1
                            considerable corn, although exportable surplus is proving very much less
                            than we contemplated. It is absolutely critical that they should draw
                            their grain supplies except corn from India, Australia and the Argentine
                            and that no supplies should be pledged to other neutrals from North
                            America.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>